{
  "texts": [
    "When the medium becomes nonperturbative, a nonperturbative determination is needed.",
    "Due to the use of the optical limit there is also a upper limit on the temperature since the optical limit assumes that the binding energy of states is small compared to π T. • Quantum features The Boltzmann equation for quarkonium is derived from the open quantum system in the quantum optical limit, with a systematic semi-classical (gradient) expansion.",
    "Quantum corrections to the recombination term have been worked out but not yet implemented.",
    "There is no quantum correction to the dissociation term [130,131].",
    "• Regeneration The recombination is formulated in the open quantum system approach (quantum optical limit) and thus it is consistent with the description of dissociation [129][130][131]."
  ]
}